 

AR-Based Heritage and Treasure Hunt
Project Overview
AR-Based Heritage and Treasure Hunt is an innovative application that combines Augmented Reality (AR), GPS, and gamification to create an interactive learning experience at historical and cultural sites. Users visit heritage locations, scan markers or monuments using their smartphone camera, and view virtual 3D models, historical information, animations, and clues overlaid on the real world. They solve puzzles and complete treasure hunt challenges while learning about the site's history.

Problem Statement
Traditional methods of exploring heritage sites often rely on information boards or guides, which may not fully engage visitors, especially younger audiences. There is a need for a more interactive, educational, and enjoyable way to experience historical places.

